    <text>
        <body>
             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">ᚃᚓᚇᚐᚁᚐ<unclear reason="damage">ᚏ</unclear></name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><supplied reason="lost">ᚋᚐ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ᚊ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ᚔ</supplied></w>  <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"̣ unit="stroke"/>ᚂᚄ<supplied reason="lost">ᚋ</supplied>
                    <lb n="2" style="text-direction:up"/><w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋᚑᚉᚑᚔ</w> <name nymRef="#?">ᚑᚇᚏ</name>
                    <lb n="3" style="text-direction:up"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/>ᚏᚓᚐ</persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">VEDABA<unclear reason="damage">R</unclear></name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><supplied reason="lost">MA</supplied><unclear reason="damage">Q</unclear><supplied reason="lost">I</supplied></w>  <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"̣ unit="stroke"/>LS<supplied reason="lost">M</supplied>
                    <lb n="2" style="text-direction:up"/><w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">MOCOI</w> <name nymRef="#?">ODR</name>
                    <lb n="3" style="text-direction:up"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/>REA</persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app n="1">
                        <note>Macalister notes that the H-half of 1R gone: only three scores of the Q remaining. Room for the I of MAQI and seven more scores (H-scores and vowels only) : H-half of 2M gone - this letter, which is at the bottom of the second line, is, in any case, faintly scratched and doubtful. The third line of writing (MOCOI ODR) perfect: no vowel between the D and the R. Top of fourth line of writing chipped away - room for 14 scores (B-scores and vowels only) (1945, 288-9). Macalister's M of MAQI, along with the second M following LS, are not discernible on the 3d model.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>'of Fíadbarr son of ? descendant of Odr...?'</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The personal name appears to be a compound with the element <distinct xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/5416">barr</ref></distinct> 'top, head (chief?), hair of the head', commonly occurring in ogham inscriptions (McManus 1991, 102-3) and the element <distinct xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/21886">fíad</ref></distinct> 'wild' (Ziegler 1994, 242, 118), applied to wild animals in particular and with <distinct xml:lang="sga">barr</distinct> 'antlers?' here possibly referring to a stag. Unfortunately, the kin group name doesn't survive in tact but perhaps refers to the <distinct xml:lang="sga">Odraige</distinct> (McManus 1991, 111).</p>
            </div>
